HEADWORD: Unsacrament
<hw>Un*sac"ra*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>sacrament</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of
sacramental character or efficacy; <as>as, to <ex>unsacrament</ex> the
rite of baptism</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
